gomodel:SYNGO_2553  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" , "Rationale: Fig.4: \"Electron micrographs demonstrating the subcellular localization of ml receptor protein\"\n- \" Electron micrograph of a spiny dendrite (d) illustrating dispersal of reaction product amid the microtubules and a spine with dense label in its neck and also at the postsynaptic density (arrow).\"\n- \"A dendrite (d) containing a deposit of reaction product (arrow) localized postsynaptically at a synapse with an axon terminal (a) forming a symmetrical synapse. F, Electron micrograph of an unlabeled dendrite (d) giving rise to a labeled spine (s).\"\n- \"H, Axospinous synapse between an unlabeled axon terminal (a) and an m I -positive spine head. The postsynaptic density (arrow) appears intensely labeled with DAB reaction product. I\"\n- \"J, Electron micrograph demonstrating presynaptic localization of m 1 receptor protein in an axon terminal (m) forming an asymmetrical synapse with an m 1 -immunoreactive spine (s).\"\n\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: \"Twelve young adult male Sprague-Dawley (Harlan) rats were deeply anesthetized ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2553" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

